channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: NEW: Barack Obama to Endorse Kamala Harris for President
Anti-Israel protesters descend on White House as Biden meets with Netanyahu
item.description: Anti-Israel protesters marched on the White House with gallons of red paint as Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu visited President Biden.

item.title: Hawley Whistleblower: USSS Refused Drones Before Trump Shooting
item.description: The U.S. Secret Service refused offers to use drones at former President Donald Trump's rally in Pennsylvania before the failed assassination attempt there, a whistleblower told Sen. Josh Hawley, R-Mo.

item.title: After Promoting Fiery 2020 Protests, Harris Condemns Vandalism, Hamas Support, and Flag Burning
'Woke' political, college leaders set stage for pro-Hamas DC protest: lawmaker
item.description: Republican Rep. Carlos Giménez says blame for the anti-Israel protests that erupted in Washington, D.C., lies "squarely on the shoulders" of "woke" leaders who failed to act.

item.title: Sen. Grassley Releases More Video From Trump Shooting
item.description: Law enforcement personnel are heard discussing the need for a drone to inspect and secure an onsite water tower in the minutes following the attempted assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump, bodycam video released Thursday shows.

item.title: House Passes Resolution Condemning Performance of 'Border Czar' Kamala
Trump's new book 'Save America' chronicles first-term triumphs, outlines blueprint for a winning second
item.description: EXCLUSIVE: Former President Trump is releasing his third official book since leaving office—a photo book filled with images to highlight the "great success" of the United States under his leadership, telling Fox News Digital that it represents the "power" that the country "will have again" if he is re-elected in November.

item.title: Ofir Akunis to Newsmax: 'I'm Worried' About the United States
item.description: Ofir Akunis, consul general for Israel in New York, told Newsmax on Thursday that the protests surrounding Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's speech in Washington, D.C., have him "worried" about the United States.

item.title: The Jill Biden Revenge Tour Is One to Watch, While Obama Reworks His Plan for Democrat Dominance
VP Harris finally reacts to DC violence, hours after flag burning by anti-Israel agitators
item.description: Vice President Harris condemned the rioting that took place in Washington, D.C. Wednesday, that included anti-Israel demonstrations and flag burning.

item.title: 6 Dems Vote With GOP to Condemn Harris on Border
item.description: Six Democrats joined every House Republican to pass a resolution Thursday strongly condemning Vice President - and anointed Border Czar - Kamala Harris for her failure to secure the United States border.

item.title: California Dreamin' - Newsom Orders Cleanup of Homeless Encampments
Six House Dems vote with GOP to condemn Kamala Harris for 'border czar' role
item.description: The House of Representatives voted to condemn Vice President Kamala Harris' role as the Biden administration's "border czar."

item.title: Kamala Harris Releases First Ad; Aims at Trump Legal Battles
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris released her first presidential campaign ad Thursday, taking aim at former President Donald Trump's legal battles.
